[Duke star](https://www.foxnews.com/category/sports/ncaa/duke-blue-devils) quarterback Darian Mensah changed his mind at the last minute and entered the transfer portal hours before it closed.

Mensah, 20, submitted his paperwork to transfer Friday, just before the midnight deadline for FBS and FCS players to enter. In December, Mensah said he would return to Duke for his redshirt junior season after contemplating declaring for the [NFL Draft.](https://www.foxnews.com/category/sports/nfl-draft)

Instead of returning for his second season with the Blue Devils, Mensah will be looking for a new college team.

