Duke Blue Devils quarterback Darian Mensah (10) looks to throw in the second quarter against the Virginia Cavaliers during the 2025 ACC Championship Game at Bank of America Stadium in Charlotte, North Carolina, on Dec. 6, 2025. (Bob Donnan/Imagn Images)

"I’m forever grateful for Duke and the coaching staff. Thank you Duke family for everything. This wasn’t an easy decision, but after talking with my family, I believe it’s in my best interest to enter the transfer portal," Mensah posted [to X.](https://x.com/DarianMensah/status/2012281535240511847?s=20)

He was reportedly set to enter the second year of a two-year deal that would pay him up to $4 million, according [to ESPN.](https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/47633503/duke-qb-darian-mensah-changes-mind-eyes-portal-sources-say) Mensah’s decision to leave Duke on the final day of the transfer portal leaves Duke in a tough position, as they have little available options in the portal to replace him.

